# Photo Studio Pivot — Tracking & Git Discipline

GridMenu is pivoting to an AI food photo studio. Requirements, status tracking, and workflow
docs live in `docs/pivot/`.

## Tracker upkeep (mandatory)

When work builds, changes, or deviates from anything in
`docs/pivot/GridMenu_Photo_Studio_Pivot_Requirements_2026-07-16.md`:

1. Update the matching status row(s) in `docs/pivot/PIVOT_TRACKER.md` (traceability tables and
   chunk log) **in the same commit** as the work.
2. Record any deviation from the requirements document, or any new product decision, as a new
   dated row in the tracker's Decisions log. Never rewrite old decision rows.
3. If a new chunk of work starts, add it to the chunk log and create
   `docs/pivot/BUILD_PLAN_CHUNK_NN.md` before implementing.

## Git workflow (user needs guidance)

The user has limited git experience. Follow `docs/pivot/GIT_WORKFLOW.md`:

- One short-lived branch per chunk, named `studio/chunk-NN-<slug>`, branched from up-to-date
  `main` and merged back promptly. Do not create long-lived branches.
- Proactively tell the user which branch work is happening on, and spell out any git commands
  they need to run themselves rather than assuming knowledge.
- Never run destructive git commands (`reset --hard`, `push --force`, history rewrites) without
  explicit approval.
- Production deploys are manual (`main` does not auto-deploy). If a change requires env vars or
  migrations in production, flag the relevant steps from the deployment checklist in
  `docs/pivot/GIT_WORKFLOW.md`.
